FBIS4-55054 "dreeu090_p_94007" FBIS-EEU-94-090 Daily Report 7 May 1994 POLAND Japan Resumes Short-Term Credit Guarantees Japan Resumes Short-Term Credit Guarantees LD0705132594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1300 GMT 7 May 94 LD0705132594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network Polish BFN [Text] Eijiro Hata, Japanese minister of international trade and industry, who met with Deputy Prime Minister Grzegorz Kolodko today, announced the resumption of short-term credit guarantees for Poland. Minister Hata said that prompt servicing of the Polish foreign debt is a condition for the further improvement of financial relations with Japan. During the meeting, Deputy Prime Minister Kolodko and Minister Hata discussed the latest plans by Japanese firms to invest in Poland, the problems of bilateral trade exchange, and Japanese technical aid for Poland.
